  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Turkey's CBI process is remarkably efficient—one of the fastest in the world. From property purchase to citizenship can be 3-6 months with proper preparation.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Citizenship by Investment Process</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Property Selection & Purchase</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Find property worth $400,000+. Due diligence essential—work with reputable agent and lawyer. Get official valuation report (SPK-licensed appraiser). Complete purchase and title transfer (tapu).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Conformity Certificate</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply for Conformity Certificate from General Directorate of Land Registry. This confirms property meets CBI requirements. Property gets 3-year sale restriction annotation (takyidat).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Residence Permit</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply for residence permit (ikamet) while in Turkey. Need: passport, property deed, insurance, photos, application form. Usually processed in 1-2 months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Citizenship Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Submit citizenship application through Provincial Directorate of Population and Citizenship Affairs. Include: Conformity Certificate, property docs, police clearance, family documents if applicable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Background Check & Approval</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Turkish authorities conduct security check. Processing: 2-4 months typically. Receive approval decision from Council of Ministers (now delegated to local authorities for CBI).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Citizenship & Passport</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Upon approval, receive Turkish citizenship certificate. Register with Nüfus (population registry). Apply for Turkish passport (2-4 weeks). Now full Turkish citizen with passport.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Family inclusion:</strong> Spouse and children under 18 can be included in the same application at no additional investment. They receive citizenship together. Adult children must apply separately. Parents of main applicant not automatically included.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

