  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Verifying Valuation Before Purchase</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Property must appraise at $400,000+ by SPK-licensed appraiser. Sale price isn't enough—official valuation matters. Get valuation first, then complete purchase. Some properties are overpriced relative to official appraisal.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Buying Previously Foreign-Owned Property</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Property must not have been owned by a foreigner who used it for citizenship previously. Fresh title from Turkish seller or developer required. Due diligence essential—some properties have been "recycled" inappropriately.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Trying to Sell Before 3 Years</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Property has 3-year sale restriction (takyidat). If you sell early, citizenship can be revoked. Don't buy expecting quick exit—plan to hold for 3+ years. You can rent it out, but cannot sell.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Ignoring Currency Risk</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Turkish Lira is volatile. While $400K property is priced in USD, ongoing costs (maintenance, taxes, management) are in Lira. Rental income in Lira may not match USD expectations. Currency can work for or against you.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Male Military Service</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Turkish male citizens (including naturalized) have military service obligation. Exemption available for those over 22 who haven't lived in Turkey, but requires payment (~$10,000). Understand this before applying for male family members.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

